chniques intended to increase the heart, lungs, and circulatory system\'s efficiency. By engaging in these programs, individuals build endurance, regulate blood flow, and optimize oxygen delivery to various parts of the body. At </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Neurigo 360</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">, our experts customize these conditioning plans based on a person’s health status, age, and medical needs, ensuring safe yet impactful results.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The human heart is essentially a muscle, and like any muscle, it grows stronger when trained properly. Cardiovascular conditioning not only strengthens the heart’s pumping ability but also makes the entire circulatory system more resilient. This translates to reduced fatigue, enhanced energy levels, and lower risks of lifestyle-related conditions such as hypertension, diabetes, and obesity.</span></p><h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(67, 67, 67